{"title": "Shivratri (the Night of Shiva)", "description": "LibriVox volunteers bring you 14 recordings of Shivratri (the Night of Shiva) by Laurence Hope.<br>\r\nThis was the Fortnightly Poetry project for November 9, 2025.   <br> ------<br>\r\nViolet Nicolson, otherwise known as Adela Florence Nicolson (n\u00e9e Cory), was an English poet who wrote under the pseudonym Laurence Hope. In the early 1900s, she became a best-selling author.\r\nAdela married Colonel Malcolm Hassels Nicolson.  A talented linguist, he introduced her to his love of India and native customs and food, which she began to share. This widely gave the couple a reputation for being eccentric. On the Zhob Valley expedition of 1890 she followed her husband through the passes of the Afghan border disguised as a Pathan boy. - Summary by Wikipedia", "duration": 1530, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10161", "name": "Laurence Hope"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/shivratri_2511.poem_librivox/shivratri_2511.jpg", "copyright_year": "1910", "genres": ["Multi-version (Weekly and Fortnightly poetry)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "David Lawrence"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Shivratri - read by BK", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shivratri_2511.poem_librivox/shivratri_hope_bk_64kb.mp3", "duration": 122}, {"section": 2, "title": "Shivratri - read by BWC", "readers": [17576], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shivratri_2511.poem_librivox/shivratri_hope_bwc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 104}, {"section": 3, "title": "Shivratri - read by CG", "readers": [20417], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shivratri_2511.poem_librivox/shivratri_hope_cg_64kb.mp3", "duration": 114}, {"section": 4, "title": "Shivratri - read by DC", "readers": [16764], "path": "https://